<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<worksheet >
    <title>EL-3 Modeling with Exponential Functions</title>
  <introduction>
    <p>Complete both parts to get M. Complete one part with progress on the other to get P.</p>
  </introduction>
  <page>
    <exercise workspace="2.5in">
      <introduction><p>The mass of a sample of a radioactive substance decays according to the function <m>M(t) = 80\left(\frac{1}{2}\right)^{\frac{t}{15}}</m>, where <m>M(t)</m> is the mass in grams and <m>t</m> is the time in years.</p>
    <p><em>Set up and solve each of the following. Leave your answers as integers, simplified fractions, or in terms of natural logarithms.</em></p>
  </introduction>
      <task><statement><p>What is the mass of the sample after 45 years?</p></statement></task>
      <task><statement><p>How many years will it take for the mass of the sample to decay to 10 grams?</p></statement></task>
    </exercise>
    
  </page>
</worksheet>